oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Problems and Opportunities in the Cattle Business
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Finney, Wray
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Thanks very much, Jim, ladies and gentlemen. It is a pleasure for me to be here today. I follow a long line of very impressive speakers. John White I have known several years, and I always hate to follow John, but in this particular case today, I am glad I do. I have a few choice words to say about the USDA. And John is unfortunately not here to defend himself, he has already gone back to Washington. And, if he had been after me, my speech would probably not been as good.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: American Association of Bovine Practitioners Conference Proceedings; 1977; 14-19
